- Responsible for business development, marketing and recruitment activities for city roll-out;
- Implementing uniform working-processes, adapted to the local environment and variables. 
- Due to Covid19, the Dusseldorf location was terminated.

Acting as a crucial factor in the development of the Kornit Digital service care centre & responsible for the end2end daily operation, adding value to the service provided to customers through implementing structure and organization (examples: service level agreements, service targets, working manuals, on boarding programs, applications & systems, training programs).

-      Leading team of 17 highly trained engineers and coordinators. 6 acting as first response point for 
       end-customers and distributors in the backoffice and 11 technical field-engineers based across 
       EMEA;
-      Responsible for the planning, logistics, execution and tracking of 15+ customer on-site visits across 
       EMEA per week, within budget and according to priority, including first-time system instalations; 
-      On-going improvement, controlling and monitoring of the services rendered by Kornit and its interntional 
        service-partners to the end customers and ensuring the fulfilment of the prescribed 
        quality standards;
-	Delivering parts of the annual budget planning (costs projections & forecasts)      
-      Developing and implementing improvement initiatives to enhance inter-departemental collaboration e.g. by introducing regular sessions and ensuring the creation of written process guidelines;
-	Creating SLA's, setting the right targets and rolling out effective and updated work-processes 
        adapted to the present situation of the company;
-       Implementing organized internal documentation databank, including the creation and updating of 
        manuals and guidelines;
-       Reshaping of critical internal procedures such as on-boarding programs and training programs;
-       Creating meaningful, long-lasting relationships with end customers, partners and distributors;
-       Responsible for on-boarding of 70% of the present team.

Acting as the leader, coach and mentor to a team of 6 multi-national 1st Line Managers & +150 agents. 

Responsible for a smooth and succesfull relationship with the client through continuous contact and proactively anticipating the clients' needs to be able to deliver before it is asked. 

Responsibilities and tasks:
• Responible for the set-up and ramp-up of the customer service center in Lisbon for the largest online store in the Netherlands ;
• Recruiting & interviewing +400 candidates and hiring +150 recruits, 6 supervisors.

• Developing, implementing and overseeing the training program of +150 recruits;
• Determining operational strategies by conducting needs assessments, performance reviews, capacity planning and 2 week training on-site at customer location;
• Maintaining and increasing customer satisfaction results through continuously organizing motivational campaigns where agents are motivated to achieve through games and competition; 
• Maintaining and improving call center operations by identifying and resolving problems, preparing and completing action plans and managing system and process improvement and quality assurance programs;
• Contributing information and analysis to organizational strategic plans and reviews;
• Continuously identifying outliers, risks and opportunities for daily strategic decisions;
• Reporting in MBR's and QBR's to evaluate and review performances;
• Communicating and ensuring compliance of the processes associated with our clients and global requirements;
